    <div class="post" id="sweeper-keeper">
        <h3>Sweeper-Keeper</h3>
        <p>
            A 'sweeper keeper' is a player that seeks to control the space behind his respective back-line. 
            The role involves keeping resolutely close to your defenders far more often than usual, keeping on your toes for the majority of each match, 
            and providing quick counter-attacking throws with hastened speed and efficiency. 

            In other words, the role of the sweeper keeper is to act as an eleventh outfield player. 
            Someone who isn’t scared of running head-first into battle whenever the situation calls for it, 
            yet a player who is equally well-versed in maintaining only the highest levels of concentration for each subsequent ninety minutes of football.

            The desired goal-keeper must be technical, remarkably self-aware, and above all else – wholeheartedly confident when saving their team from the brink of defeat. 

            At times the ploy can prove somewhat hazardous, fraught with danger and a tricky sense of uncertainty if the goal-keeper in question is clearly not up for the job. 

            In the end the ‘sweeper-keeper’ takes no prisoners, and most football onlookers simply can’t help but love him for it. 
            Sometimes, life between the sticks is one of great magnitude. 
            A trial of unpredictability and excitement, all wrapped up in one truly memorable ensemble.
        </p>
