    <div class="post" id="false-nine">
        <h3>False 9</h3>
        <p>
            The false 9 is essentially a striker who drops deeps, i.e he drifts back into midfield rather staying around the penalty box for various tactical reasons.

            Generally with a traditional center forward,one of the center back tracks him and the spare one covers for him, 
            but with a false 9 both the center backs during the build up play are left free. 

            This causes confusion as they are caught in two minds on whether they need to follow the false 9 into midfield or 
            do they stick with their partner and maintain their defensive line. 

            If the centre backs decided to withdraw from following him, they left him with enough time and space between their lines to cause significant damage. 

            That said, a false 9 needs superb technical ability and the cerebral ability to exploit space. He is not a typical battering ram nor is he a poacher. 

            The False 9 has to have multiple skills in order to perfect the role. 
            
            The player should have good dribbling skills, good awareness, long and short range finishing. They do not necessarily require strength or heading ability.
        </p>
